rComments: Professor Oesch is a good lecturer but not a likeable person. He gets very bothered by people talking during class and likes to call them out during lecture. This course seems easy on the surface but they grade tough because it is a first year Rotman-required course that determines your acceptance into the program. Boring course.

John Oesch is a simple man. You respect him in lectures and and he respects you back. His lectures are average and the examples he uses in lectures are from his own experiences which is good. His class is boring ... but he's doing his job. John post slides on time unlike... Khan who says he will post it and posts it 1 day before exams.

John is the epitome of average. His lectures are extremely dry and very optional. His midterm test is a regurgitation of the textbook and slides. Was curved down 10%, but the difficulty was comparable to grade 12 social studies. Would recommend this class - don't go, study night before, do well.

Very clear, direct professor. There is a sizeable amount of reading, but I don't think it's unfair. Gives relevant real life examples of concepts he discusses and VERY clear instructions for what will be tested, and he's very nice to talk to in person! 11/10 would take his classes again!

John is probably the worst professor in first-year Rotman; his lectures are extremely boring, irrelevant, and add nothing to your education. All questions on the tests were directly taken from the textbook so just read that and you'll be fine. Other than that, he seems like a pretty decent guy -- just a terrible instructor.

John is a very polite and simple man. He is very clear on what is tested, how many of each chapter. Every thing on his slides and lectures is also clear and on point. Read the textbook, don't call him Prof, and you'll be fine.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Test heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: John Oesch gives extremely boring lectures that you usually don't need to go to. He seems like an alright guy, just boring and doesn't add much to your education at least in RSM100.

Professor Oesch was decent. I found his lectures a bit dry and boring and the 1 thing you'll definitely take from this course is his farm lol. Go to lectures and read the textbook as this course is PURELY based on memorization of the text, online required readings and content covered in class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I LOVE JOHN!
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: He was an alright prof. You should go to lectures because some stuff will be on the exam, that are not otherwise covered in the textbook. But the exams are heavily textbook based, so do your readings and it's a 4.0! Also, he talks about his farm and family alot, but that makes the class a little more comfortable.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Professor Osech was an alright professor. Spent way too much time talking about his "beautiful bride", kids, and his farm. He gives good examples relevant examples though! Should read the textbook.
Not much to say

Professor Oesch has been a good instructor of the material. In the lectures, there are many examples given to support the topics. If you miss a class, you miss out on the examples which he gives (which are on the exams). The quizzes are based solely on the textbook. If you don't read the textbook, you might not get the best marks.

Good prof, really concise and clear when he teaches although the material does get a bit boring at times due to the long lectures. The overall class was enjoyable and learned quite a lot as well as he has a good sense of humor
Terrible Lecturer - Incredibly boring and tough to stay awake.

boring class, disappointment considering the expectation of the quality of materials I was expecting to learn going into the class. Professor was just okay but nothing special. Felt like a better job could have been done to convey the main points and substantiate them in class instead of over-focusing on deliverables
He is a nice teacher, keeps everyone interested in class and gives awesome examples. Take his class!

He is a decent lecturer. The course material was usually boring but he threw some jokes in sometimes. His course involves plenty of memorization; you will have to memorize the entire text book basically, it's not as easy as it sounds. Overall a mediocre experience.
Professor Oesch was a bit boring to be honest - he pretty much reads from the lecture slides. I  do not recommend taking his morning classes.

Boring classes. Only went to 2 classes in term and got over 85 percent on the midterm. If you are fairly intelligent, the test should be easy. However, he sometimes tests you on the most ridiculous stuff (not on textbook).
Very clear and very committed to teaching the information in his course. His lectures were filled with relevant content and tips. A serious, top-notch professor.

The content of his lectures are a bit boring, and a lot of exam questions are found in the text or from past years. However, overall it is an easy course if you read the textbook and go to class 80% of the time.
My favorite professor so far. This guy has a great sense of humor, and he made RSM100 a fun class to attend(the only class that I dont wanna skip..). Impressive overall. Luv you John!

He is very organized with the slides and lectures.As for the tests and exams,he will tell how many questions will be tested on each chapters,which makes the heavy reading of the course easier.Overall nice prof!

for those who are wondering how to pronounce my name: its john. same old joke lol. anyways, only had him for 3 months, teaches straight from textbook so lectures redundant, study the terminology and youre set. final only includes his section so thats good.
don't like him, he was rude. And he curved our final exam grade downwards

Overall decent prof, takes some time to warm up to his lecture style (arrogance aside), expects you to know "everything" for mid-terms & exams. Study both the textbook(make notes) and the lecture notes and you should be fine. Profs Dungan & Zuliani cover both mid-terms but Oesch gets all 50% of the final, so don't neglect his portion of the course.

Great prof, no nonsense, no bs. Very clear in his presentation as well. He says that for U of T business, we are there to win, to make money, and to work hard. Those who did not like John may want to reconsider their major. He also has the odd funny joke too. Overall a good guy
Awesome prof, he is a god send after Elisa Zuliani

I really didnt like Professor Oesch at all.He was boring, unenthusiastic, the exact opposite of Mr Dungan, who taught the first few weeks of Com 110, who I might add is brilliant. Professor Oesch had somewhat hard tests but 1 good thing about him was that he raised our marks and increased the class average from a 60 to 70, he can be funny at times
